text: Urlabari is a city and municipality in the Morang District in the Province 1 of southeastern Nepal that makes it the second largest city in Morang District after Biratnagar. At the time of the 1991 Nepal census, it had a population of 18224. At the time of the 2011 Nepal census, it had a population of 35,166 and 8,165 households. It is found 60 km eastern part of metropolitan city Biratnagar. == References == Category:Cities in Nepal Category:Municipalities of Nepal
